Job Description:
VIGILINT is a premier provider of international health protection, providing advisory, logistics, medical operations, and crisis management services to high-net-worth individuals, Fortune 500 companies, and government clients. Our world-class physicians, subject matter experts, and operational staff work side-by-side to solve complex medical emergencies around the globe. The nature of our work requires top performance and the utmost discretion.

VIGILINT is seeking Full-Time Operations Analysts to support our 24/7 Medical Operations Center coordinating logistics, medical care, and evacuations. Analysts also conduct medical intelligence gathering, medical surveillance, and open-source research.

Candidates must be innovative, independent problem solvers and be able to work successfully in a semi-stressful work environment. VIGILINT will provide training in crisis management, medical contingency planning, intelligence gathering, and telemedicine operations.

New employees will work closely with experienced leaders from military, medical operations, concierge medical, and logistics communities.

The Operations Center is staffed on a 24/7 basis, requiring continuous employee coverage. Employees will be assigned to work days, nights, weekends, and holidays.

Selection will close once VIGILINT has filled available positions. Successful candidates will be expected to relocate to the Raleigh-Durham area within 4 to 6 weeks of offer.

Requirements

Required Qualifications:

 Bachelor’s degree from an accredited, four-year college or university or 4+ years of military and/or directly relevant work experience in medical logistics/planning, civil affairs, or intelligence

 Strong critical thinking, writing, and oral communications skills;

 Ability to manage crises with composure;

 Ability to handle sensitive information and materials with discretion;

 Intermediate, advanced, or native proficiency in one or more foreign languages;

 Background/interest in operational medicine, international security, or emergency

preparedness;

 US citizen and able to obtain a Secret-level security clearance; and a

 Valid U.S. passport (or ability to obtain).

Desired Qualifications:

 Experience/study in: international relations, security studies, emergency management or

similar;

 Medical background or interest (e.g. EMT, Paramedic, RN, pre-med, health studies, etc.)

 Prior research skills; and

 Prior supervisory or leadership experience.

Benefits

VIGILINT operates on principles of fair and just employment practices. We will provide successful candidates with the following benefits:

 Operations Analyst hiring range: $47,500 - $55,000, based on education and experience;

 Medical, Dental and vision insurance

 401(k) with employer matching;

 Paid sick leave & vacation leave;

 On-site gym;

 Moderately flexible work schedule

VIGILINT is an equal opportunity employer and, as such, provides employment opportunities without regard to race, color, religion, national origin, sex (including pregnancy), age, disability, veteran or military status, genetic information, or other legally protected characteristics.

APEX bridges the gap between sensor and analyst in the evolving field of intelligence analysis. APEX tightly couples analysts, operators, and engineers to produce an unmatched level of problem-solving capacity for any situation.

Spanning various disciplines, including geospatial intelligence (GEOINT), signals intelligence (SIGINT), and human intelligence (HUMINT) analysis, APEX analysts, operators, and engineers work with operational mission partners to deliver novel technology, tactics, techniques, and procedures (T3P), relevant and modern training, and innovative technology solutions.

If you are a motivated individual willing to tackle challenging, and interesting problems, come be a part of our dynamic team!

